Package com.rb.nonbiz.testcategories

Interface OvernightTests

All Known Subinterfaces:
Backtests, SlowClientDemos
public interface OvernightTests
This is just a category marker, so it is intentionally empty.

It is meant to separate the time-consuming tests from regular tests, so that we can only run those ones 'overnight'. Of course, it doesn't have to be overnight, but the point is that these are slow enough to take multiple hours and don't make sense to run in the typical intraday runs of unit tests (currently - March 2024 - named ExcludeSlowTestsSuite*).

This is currently mostly backtests, but can also include other slow tests, even ones that are a few seconds long, which is still too long to include in an ESTS run.
